 “you haven’t seen it yet! Pardon me for tearing you away from your sandwich, my friend, but I feel obligated to show you my new painting. The connoisseurs are going crazy over it. Come on. Of course I don’t dare ask Frank.”

Frank made a jovial bow. “You’re right, Father. Paintings perturb me.”

